<section name="Sample Projects">
<p>
The <code>samples</code> directory in Glean has a set of properties files to configure
Glean for a number of sample projects. If you are looking for what a project configuration
might look like for different types of source projects, these could give you a start.
</p>
<p>
To run any of them, you will need to download the source (links included in the
table below), andd in most cases build them (see the instructions for each, but
it it usually a case of running "<code>ant</code>" from the command line).
If you want to try running one of these, the only thing you should have to do
is update the configuration to point to the base directory where you unpacked
the project.
</p>

